HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 425
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Callaway Chaney, 2025
Top Ten Senior of Mt. Pleasant High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Callaway Chaney is one such exceptional student, who was recently named
a Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Mt. Pleasant High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Mr. Chaney has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in his remarkable high school career, Callaway Chaney has earned an
exemplary grade point average of 97 while participating in numerous extracurricular activities
and taking dual enrollment courses at Columbia State Community College; and
WHEREAS, following his graduation, Mr. Chaney plans to attend university and earn a
bachelor's degree in medicinal chemistry, and wherever he ultimately decides to study will be
greatly blessed by his outstanding academic and personal capacities; and
WHEREAS, apart from his scholastic endeavors, Mr. Chaney currently works with his
grandfather through work-based learning; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Chaney's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for his future success; and
WHEREAS, his noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for his family,
his school, and his community; and
